16:01.090 --> 16:04.137
- Play a game?

16:05.225 --> 16:07.270
- You really are capable
of keeping a secret.

16:07.314 --> 16:09.620
Four, by my count.

16:10.708 --> 16:13.146
Who the hell are you, Beck?

16:17.280 --> 16:20.196
[laughter]
- Hi, there.

16:20.240 --> 16:22.068
Hey! That's a boy.
- Oh! First try.

16:22.111 --> 16:23.199
- You're a natural.

16:23.243 --> 16:24.896
[clattering]
- Yo!

16:24.940 --> 16:28.074
- Two down.

16:28.117 --> 16:29.597
- What an arm on him.

16:29.640 --> 16:32.426
I know. I--I know I'm
embarrassing, I know.

16:32.469 --> 16:34.994
Babe, just get a shot
for the blog.

16:35.037 --> 16:37.126
- Ooh!
- [screams]

16:37.170 --> 16:38.998
- If I wasn't so
blinded by love,

16:39.041 --> 16:40.564
I would've seen the secrets

16:40.608 --> 16:42.784
right in front of me,
waiting to be uncovered.

16:42.827 --> 16:45.352
Captain Beck.
AKA, The Captain.

16:45.395 --> 16:49.747
AKA, Edward Martin Beck.

16:49.791 --> 16:51.271
The addict part was true,
I see.

16:51.314 --> 16:52.881
But he never died,
which he credits

16:52.924 --> 16:54.839
to his friends in
the NA fellowship

16:54.883 --> 16:57.190
out of St. James Church.

16:57.233 --> 16:59.279
It was there that he
not only conquered his demons

16:59.322 --> 17:01.237
but also met church rep
and divorcée,

17:01.281 --> 17:03.152
Nancy Whitesell.

17:03.196 --> 17:07.548
AKA, "The Christian News'"
Mommy Blogger of the Year.

17:07.591 --> 17:09.898
"If Ned can do it,
so can you."

17:09.941 --> 17:11.160
He became a feature
in her blog.

17:11.204 --> 17:13.075
Then, her life.

17:13.119 --> 17:16.426
Less than a year,
they were married.

17:16.470 --> 17:18.733
He really landed himself
the perfect family.

17:18.776 --> 17:21.431
If your step-mother
is to be believed.

17:21.475 --> 17:23.346
But what about you, Beck.

17:23.390 --> 17:26.088
Where do you fit
into all this?

17:26.132 --> 17:30.092
♪

17:31.050 --> 17:34.879
[brass band music]

17:34.923 --> 17:36.838
- [sighs]

17:42.278 --> 17:45.542
Your father has come
such a long way.

17:45.586 --> 17:47.327
He worked hard for it, too.

17:47.370 --> 17:48.806
- You're barking up
the wrong tree, lady,

17:48.850 --> 17:50.112
if you think
I'm gonna sit here

17:50.156 --> 17:51.244
and validate that man.

17:51.287 --> 17:54.160
Yeah, he's, uh--
he's lucky to have you.

17:54.203 --> 17:55.726
- Hm.

17:55.770 --> 17:57.946
Just goes to show you
what a good Christian household

17:57.989 --> 17:59.687
and loving family can do.

17:59.730 --> 18:01.689
- She did not just suggest
if you were more Christian

18:01.732 --> 18:04.344
he wouldn't have abandoned you
for a crack pipe.

18:05.171 --> 18:07.347
- Mommy, come watch me.

18:07.390 --> 18:10.828
- Excuse me, my dear.

18:13.353 --> 18:15.398
- [sighs]

18:17.879 --> 18:19.359
- [sighs]

18:19.402 --> 18:21.056
Your dad talk to you yet?

18:21.100 --> 18:24.059
- She's so her mother,
only less subtle.

18:24.103 --> 18:26.844
Talk to me about--
- Well, he's supposed to

18:26.888 --> 18:30.500
tell you he can't
send money anymore.

18:30.544 --> 18:32.807
But he's gonna help you
find a better job first.

18:32.850 --> 18:35.766
[sighs] Mom doesn't think
he should wait.

18:35.810 --> 18:37.942
She's so cranky.

18:37.986 --> 18:41.163
It's the hormones.

18:41.207 --> 18:44.253
Oh. I wasn't supposed
to tell you,

18:44.297 --> 18:47.517
but she's pregnant.

18:47.561 --> 18:49.171
That's why they're
fighting about it.

18:49.215 --> 18:50.825
- Great. That's great.

18:50.868 --> 18:53.784
He's starting a new family.

18:53.828 --> 18:58.528
Because fixing the one he had
obviously wasn't an option.

18:58.572 --> 19:02.489
Why would he ever do that?

19:04.360 --> 19:06.971
I'm going to find a bathroom.
I'll be right back.

19:07.015 --> 19:14.065
♪

19:15.284 --> 19:18.722
Can I get another
Timber Doodle?

19:30.430 --> 19:32.083
Uh! Bitch.

19:32.127 --> 19:35.086
[rock music]

19:35.130 --> 19:42.181
♪

19:44.313 --> 19:47.360
- Hi. Is Joe Goldberg
working today?

19:47.403 --> 19:49.971
- Joe Goldberg is not
working today.

19:50.014 --> 19:51.886
But, uh, I'm Ethan.

19:51.929 --> 19:54.323
And you would be--
- Looking for Joe.

19:54.367 --> 19:56.630
Expect him anytime soon?
- I do not.

19:56.673 --> 19:59.067
Uh, relatively speaking.
Joe's out of town.

19:59.110 --> 20:01.156
But is there anything
I can help you find?

20:01.200 --> 20:03.071
- Possibly.
I'm in the market

20:03.114 --> 20:05.552
for a first-edition copy
of "Ozma of Oz."

20:05.595 --> 20:08.076
- Oh, that's a pretty rare
critter.

20:08.119 --> 20:09.338
Uh, not sure we have it.

20:09.382 --> 20:10.774
See, books of
that pedigree we keep

20:10.818 --> 20:13.255
under lock and key
downstairs.

20:13.299 --> 20:15.605
- And you don't have the key?

20:15.649 --> 20:17.694
- Well, normally
I have the key.

20:17.738 --> 20:19.479
But I just don't
have it right now.

20:19.522 --> 20:22.221
Uh, Joe left with it. He just
forgot to give it to me.

20:22.264 --> 20:25.049
- And where is Joe?

20:25.093 --> 20:27.530
[cell phone ringing]

20:27.574 --> 20:29.576
- I thought I was supposed
to be writing.

20:29.619 --> 20:31.273
- Are you with Eight Seconds?

20:31.317 --> 20:33.406
- No, I told you.
I'm on a retreat.

20:33.449 --> 20:35.059
- Is he with you?

20:35.103 --> 20:37.148
[cell phone buzzes]

20:37.192 --> 20:38.846
- What is it, Ethan?
- Hey, bro.

20:38.889 --> 20:40.848
Uh, I know you didn't
wanna be interrupted,

20:40.891 --> 20:42.763
but, uh, this chick
was just in asking about

20:42.806 --> 20:45.635
a first ed. "Ozma of Oz."
- What are you talking about?

20:45.679 --> 20:47.768
- Joe's there, in Nyack.

20:47.811 --> 20:50.988
- What did she look like?
- Uh, 25-ish, brunette,

20:51.032 --> 20:54.035
kinda hot, but you know,
maybe that's like a type thing.

20:54.078 --> 20:55.428
- Peach Salinger.

20:55.471 --> 20:57.473
- Are you lying to me?
- Of course you are,

20:57.517 --> 20:58.692
that's what you do,

20:58.735 --> 20:59.736
lie so your life
looks better.

20:59.780 --> 21:02.086
Peach, I'm--I'm not lying.

21:02.130 --> 21:04.524
I told you,
I'm here to write. I--

21:04.567 --> 21:05.960
I can't deal
with this right now

21:06.003 --> 21:08.658
I promise I'll call you.
- And you told her I'm here?

21:08.702 --> 21:11.095
- I'm sorry, man.
Did I screw up or--

21:11.139 --> 21:13.446
- You'll know I'm here.
You may already know.

21:13.489 --> 21:16.492
- Hey, you. Oh, sorry.

21:16.536 --> 21:17.450
So sorry.

21:17.493 --> 21:19.452
- How is this explainable?

21:19.495 --> 21:22.455
Do I run?
Shit, shit, shit.

21:22.498 --> 21:25.458
[light music]

21:25.501 --> 21:32.552
♪

21:35.032 --> 21:37.121
- Joe?

21:37.165 --> 21:38.340
- Beck?

21:38.384 --> 21:40.081
What are you doing here?

21:46.435 --> 21:48.872
[fiddle music]

21:48.916 --> 21:52.267
- That's true, you are
a book seller, aren't you?

21:52.311 --> 21:55.879
- Sadly, I humiliate myself
like this annually.

21:55.923 --> 21:59.535
- Mm. Well, this is kinda
working for ya.

21:59.579 --> 22:00.667
- You mock.
- [laughs]

22:00.710 --> 22:03.539
- It's--it's fair.

22:03.583 --> 22:05.628
[sighs]

22:06.890 --> 22:09.589
I'm--I'm lying.
I'm lying to you right now.

22:09.632 --> 22:11.808
- Excuse me?
- I knew you were here.

22:11.852 --> 22:14.158
I wasn't happy with how
we left things.

22:14.202 --> 22:15.551
And apparently,
neither were you,

22:15.595 --> 22:16.639
seeing as how you were

22:16.683 --> 22:18.467
hiding out in the bathroom.
- I--I--

22:18.511 --> 22:20.121
I wasn't hiding, I swear.

22:20.164 --> 22:22.428
- We can at least agree
that I may

22:22.471 --> 22:24.604
have left you a little wanting.

22:24.647 --> 22:26.475
- Yeah--
- So, you're saying you did

22:26.519 --> 22:28.347
want it to last
longer than eight seconds?

22:28.390 --> 22:30.566
- No! I mean--yeah.
As in--

22:30.610 --> 22:32.394
- Wait, I thought
it was a race.

22:32.438 --> 22:34.178
Didn't I win?

22:34.222 --> 22:36.093
No. Um--

22:36.137 --> 22:39.401
I just--I thought it'd be nice
if I came and surprised you.

22:39.445 --> 22:41.621
And not leave you with...

22:41.664 --> 22:44.928
that memory of me for too long.

22:46.452 --> 22:48.628
- How did you, um--

22:48.671 --> 22:50.369
How did you know I was here?

22:50.412 --> 22:53.154
- Oh, well, you posted
a nature shot this morning.

22:53.197 --> 22:55.939
See that little restaurant sign
in the background?

22:55.983 --> 22:58.551
Apparently, Pops and Millie's
ain't a chain.

22:58.594 --> 23:00.466
- Mm, shocking.
Really should be.

23:00.509 --> 23:02.119
- Yeah.

23:02.163 --> 23:03.817
So I Googled it
and I saw all the information

23:03.860 --> 23:05.427
about the festival
and I figured

23:05.471 --> 23:06.776
this was probably why
you were in the area.

23:06.820 --> 23:07.908
And by the way,
this outfit

23:07.951 --> 23:09.431
is really working on you, too.

23:09.475 --> 23:11.259
- Ohh.

23:11.302 --> 23:13.435
Um--

23:13.479 --> 23:14.610
[sighs]

23:14.654 --> 23:18.092
Can you hold on
for just one second?

23:19.310 --> 23:21.704
- Hey, sweetie.
Cooper's kinda hitting a wall.

23:21.748 --> 23:23.576
We were gonna head back
and rest up before dinner.

23:23.619 --> 23:25.404
- Oh, okay. I'll find my own

23:25.447 --> 23:27.101
ride back to the hotel, so--

23:27.144 --> 23:29.669
- And who is this
handsome gentleman?

23:29.712 --> 23:32.541
- Sorry, this is--
this is Joe.

23:32.585 --> 23:35.370
He works at a book store
I go to in the city.

23:35.414 --> 23:37.328
- Well, hey, Joe.

23:37.372 --> 23:39.635
- This is my wife, Nancy.
I'm--I'm Ned, Beck's dad.

23:39.679 --> 23:42.203
- Hi.
- Hey, nice to meet you both.

23:42.246 --> 23:44.771
- You're welcome to join us
for dinner, Joe.

23:44.814 --> 23:47.861
- Yes! Totally.
If you can.

23:47.904 --> 23:50.690
[sighs]
- I--I'd love to.

23:50.733 --> 23:53.432
- We'll see you then.

23:54.737 --> 23:56.696
- Okay, uh--

23:56.739 --> 23:57.958
I can explain.

23:58.001 --> 24:00.874
Um--

24:00.917 --> 24:01.744
[sighs]

24:01.788 --> 24:04.225
One day, when I was, um, 12,

24:04.268 --> 24:07.707
I got home from school
before my brother and sister.

24:07.750 --> 24:09.578
My mom was at work.

24:09.622 --> 24:13.539
So I go into the basement
to play "Mario Brothers"

24:13.582 --> 24:17.456
And I, uh--I find...

24:17.499 --> 24:19.632
my father...

24:19.675 --> 24:23.766
unconscious, with a needle
in his arm.

24:25.638 --> 24:28.641
I thought he was dead.

24:28.684 --> 24:30.599
- I'm so sorry

24:30.643 --> 24:31.644
you had to go through that.

24:31.687 --> 24:34.342
- I mean, he survived it.

24:34.385 --> 24:38.651
And--which, of course,
was this amazing thing.

24:38.694 --> 24:41.958
So when he disappeared on us
because he relapsed,

24:42.002 --> 24:43.699
I just--

24:43.743 --> 24:45.962
I couldn't believe it.

24:46.006 --> 24:51.533
Right then and there,
I decided he was dead.

24:51.577 --> 24:54.362
Which is why I told you he was,
which is...

24:54.405 --> 24:55.711
[sighs]

24:55.755 --> 24:58.932
totally wrong, I mean,
who does that?

24:58.975 --> 25:02.544
[chuckles] The first deep,
personal thing

25:02.588 --> 25:04.372
I tell you is a total lie.

25:04.415 --> 25:06.592
- Well, hang on. That's--

25:06.635 --> 25:08.768
- No, I get it if you
are horrified

25:08.811 --> 25:10.596
and think I'm a total fraud
and liar

25:10.639 --> 25:12.598
and want nothing to do with me.

25:12.641 --> 25:15.557
- After everything
you've been through?

25:15.601 --> 25:16.645
I get it.

25:16.689 --> 25:19.300
I'm sorry.

25:20.649 --> 25:22.259
- [chuckles]

25:22.303 --> 25:24.523
You're sorry?

25:26.525 --> 25:28.527
- I am.

25:30.224 --> 25:32.966
- Anyway, I was--
I was at Brown

25:33.009 --> 25:35.795
and he tracked me down
to say he had gotten clean.

25:35.838 --> 25:37.797
And then he says
he wants to help

25:37.840 --> 25:41.278
with my school
and some of my bills.

25:41.322 --> 25:45.718
Like dad amends.
So I bury my resentment

25:45.761 --> 25:47.807
and start having
lunches with him

25:47.850 --> 25:50.897
and doing stupid
shit like this.

25:50.940 --> 25:53.508
Playing the dutiful daughter.

25:53.552 --> 25:57.381
Enduring this nauseatingly
perfect new family of his.

25:57.425 --> 26:00.167
- I'm sure they're not perfect.
- Believe me,

26:00.210 --> 26:02.256
they are.
- Well, I guess

26:02.299 --> 26:04.650
I'll find out tonight.
- No. [laughs]

26:04.693 --> 26:06.216
I'm not subjecting you to that.

26:06.260 --> 26:09.045
I'll just--I'll tell them
you had to go back.

26:09.089 --> 26:11.308
Book emergency.
- I'd be on board,

26:11.352 --> 26:13.789
but that would be
so un-Victorian of me.

26:13.833 --> 26:16.575
The virtuous maiden
is supposed to be rescued

26:16.618 --> 26:19.839
by the dashing,
sometimes broody

26:19.882 --> 26:21.797
altogether charming hero.
- [laughs]

26:21.841 --> 26:25.453
And who is that? Is that--
is that meant to be you?

26:25.496 --> 26:26.759
[laughter]

26:26.802 --> 26:27.803
- But that boat,
she can take it.

26:27.847 --> 26:28.761
You know.
- No, no, I know,

26:28.804 --> 26:29.936
I know it well.

26:29.979 --> 26:31.198
I don't know
if Beck's told you,

26:31.241 --> 26:32.460
but I captained
the Nantucket Ferry

26:32.503 --> 26:33.679
for 16 years.

26:33.722 --> 26:34.810
- I did not know--
see, now,

26:34.854 --> 26:35.898
I feel like I've been telling

26:35.942 --> 26:37.683
Mickey Mantle
how to hold a bat.

26:37.726 --> 26:38.771
- Oh, please.

26:38.814 --> 26:39.989
- Do you sail, too?

26:40.033 --> 26:41.600
- Oh, God, no.
Never had the patience for it.

26:41.643 --> 26:43.819
- Oh, Dad, you know your way
around a sailboat.

26:43.863 --> 26:45.734
- Well, enough to know
that I'm all thumbs.

26:45.778 --> 26:47.040
Yeah, I've been out
a couple times.

26:47.083 --> 26:49.608
- You don't remember
the renters next door?

26:49.651 --> 26:51.653
They had that Sunfish
they let you take out.

26:51.697 --> 26:55.396
The Murphys. Their cars were
always blocking the driveway.

26:55.439 --> 26:57.833
- How's life in
the big city, dear?

26:57.877 --> 27:00.401
- It's great.
Thanks for asking.

27:00.444 --> 27:02.751
Oh, and we broke our
centerboard that one time.

27:02.795 --> 27:05.362
And--and the current took us,
like, halfway to Long Island.

27:05.406 --> 27:07.538
- Eh--what'd I say?
Not much of a sailor.

27:07.582 --> 27:09.802
- [laughs] But you do,
you remember it, right?

27:09.845 --> 27:11.542
I mean, it was pouring.

27:11.586 --> 27:14.633
I learned every swear word
in the book that day.

27:16.896 --> 27:18.593
- I don't think he remembers,
dear.

27:18.637 --> 27:21.683
- I think he can
speak for himself, Nancy.

27:21.727 --> 27:24.686
God, you know, you don't--
you don't have to protect him.

27:24.730 --> 27:26.427
Okay, he's--he's not a child.

27:26.470 --> 27:28.821
[silverware clanks]
- You're one to talk.

27:28.864 --> 27:30.692
- Excuse me?
- You invest nothing

27:30.736 --> 27:32.520
in this family.

27:32.563 --> 27:33.913
Nothing.

27:33.956 --> 27:35.784
Not even a call
to your father on his birthday.

27:35.828 --> 27:37.003
- You know what? Stop.

27:37.046 --> 27:38.569
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

27:38.613 --> 27:40.963
- 'Cause your father--
he's just an ATM to you.

27:41.007 --> 27:43.183
Right, Beck?
- Uh, please,

27:43.226 --> 27:44.793
let's not do this.
- Okay, I'm sorry.

27:44.837 --> 27:46.360
And what is he to you?

27:46.403 --> 27:48.492
A feature for your blog
so you can brag

27:48.536 --> 27:50.886
how you lifted him
out of the pits of despair?

27:50.930 --> 27:53.584
News flash!
He was sober when you met him.

27:53.628 --> 27:54.934
I was in the pits with him.

27:54.977 --> 27:57.937
And not because
I wasn't Christian enough.

27:57.980 --> 28:00.461
You didn't save him.

28:00.504 --> 28:01.549
You think he'll fall over

28:01.592 --> 28:03.072
if you pull your hand
out of his ass?

28:03.116 --> 28:06.075
- Guinevere! Enough.
- [sighs]

28:06.119 --> 28:07.294
- What the hell
are you looking at?

28:07.337 --> 28:08.556
- Guinevere.
- Do not talk

28:08.599 --> 28:09.775
to my daughter that way.

28:09.818 --> 28:11.820
- Okay, whatever.
I'm done.

28:11.864 --> 28:13.779
Oh, and, um...

28:13.822 --> 28:15.737
congrats on the baby.

28:15.781 --> 28:17.783
How blessed you all are.

28:17.826 --> 28:19.654
[slams table]

28:19.698 --> 28:22.657
[dark tone]

28:22.701 --> 28:25.965
♪

28:45.724 --> 28:48.291
- Do you want him dead?

28:51.251 --> 28:53.296
- What?

28:56.343 --> 29:00.129
- Kinda feels like
you and he...

29:00.173 --> 29:01.783
have some unresolved stuff.

29:01.827 --> 29:05.569
Believe me, I'm king
of unresolved family issues.

29:05.613 --> 29:09.399
I know what people splitting
feels like.

29:09.443 --> 29:10.705
[sighs]

29:10.749 --> 29:13.882
I just wonder if, uh--

29:13.926 --> 29:16.406
Look, he's here.
He's alive.

29:16.450 --> 29:20.541
Use that as an opportunity
to talk to him.

29:22.717 --> 29:26.112
Or, uh, you're a writer.

29:26.155 --> 29:27.591
Could be helpful
to write about him.

29:27.635 --> 29:30.769
Cathartic, too.
- What are you doing?

29:30.812 --> 29:31.900
- N-nothing--I don't--

29:31.944 --> 29:33.032
- Do you hear yourself
right now?

29:33.075 --> 29:34.294
I mean, who the hell are you

29:34.337 --> 29:37.036
to tell me that
I have daddy issues.

29:37.079 --> 29:38.211
You don't even know me.

29:38.254 --> 29:39.473
- Hey, Beck, hang--
hang--hang on--

29:39.516 --> 29:41.127
- Just go.

29:41.170 --> 29:44.608
Leave me alone.
I'm serious.

29:47.873 --> 29:48.917
[sighs]

29:48.961 --> 29:56.272
♪

30:07.893 --> 30:10.939
- Hey, hon.

30:10.983 --> 30:13.289
We're gonna get going.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.860
- Cool, um--

30:18.904 --> 30:22.864
Thanks for dinner.

30:22.908 --> 30:24.910
- This should cover the room.

30:39.533 --> 30:42.492
- It's hard for me
to see you with them.

30:42.536 --> 30:46.018
I keep waiting
for you to be you again.

30:46.061 --> 30:47.889
- Well, this is me, Guinevere.

30:47.933 --> 30:49.891
- No, it's not. You were--

30:49.935 --> 30:51.110
- Reckless.

30:51.153 --> 30:52.241
And out of control.

30:52.285 --> 30:54.896
And, honey,
you were a kid, you--

30:54.940 --> 30:56.724
You didn't see
what was going on.

30:56.767 --> 30:58.726
- Yes--

30:58.769 --> 31:00.467
yes, I did.

31:00.510 --> 31:03.774
And you were more
than just an addict.

31:05.167 --> 31:07.561
I miss you.

31:11.086 --> 31:14.568
[sighs] Whatever.

31:14.611 --> 31:17.179
You know, I tell people
that you're dead.

31:18.789 --> 31:22.968
Kinda feels like you did die
that day in the basement.

31:23.011 --> 31:25.971
[somber music]

31:26.014 --> 31:27.015
♪

31:27.059 --> 31:29.800
- I'm sorry you feel that way.

31:32.064 --> 31:34.109
- You were a good sailor.

31:41.160 --> 31:44.163
- Well, maybe you can
tell me about it sometime.

31:44.206 --> 31:46.992
Maybe in Vermont.

31:47.035 --> 31:49.559
Over Christmas.

31:52.388 --> 31:54.825
- Like I said,
I'll have to let you know.

31:57.132 --> 32:04.444
♪

32:11.146 --> 32:14.106
[somber pop music]

32:14.149 --> 32:18.023
♪

32:18.066 --> 32:20.112
[sighs]

32:20.155 --> 32:27.206
♪

32:41.611 --> 32:42.917
[sighs]

32:42.961 --> 32:44.701
On the plywood
over the bay window,

32:44.745 --> 32:47.574
we spray paint taunts
at Hurricane Isabel.

32:47.617 --> 32:50.011
Cow her into a tropical storm.

32:50.055 --> 32:54.363
Her moon tide, though,
carries your beach chair away.

32:58.672 --> 33:01.022
Sea glass and Springsteen.

33:01.066 --> 33:04.591
The beached whale,
the silent walk home.

33:04.634 --> 33:08.247
The grill that doesn't start
on the Fourth of July.

33:11.076 --> 33:13.817
♪

33:13.861 --> 33:18.083
The woman at the drug store
you hit on who isn't Mom.

33:18.126 --> 33:21.086
The renters
blocking the drive.

33:21.129 --> 33:25.003
The string of my sweatshirt
I gnaw on.

33:26.221 --> 33:29.094
Morning sun over Wauwinet.

33:29.137 --> 33:31.487
The red ladle over the pan.

33:31.531 --> 33:34.099
Your wrist, the perfect cant.

33:34.142 --> 33:36.449
[phone buzzes]

33:37.885 --> 33:41.628
You leave for the 8:20 to
Hyannis with one commandment.

33:41.671 --> 33:45.023
Get the batter off the ladle
while it's wet.

33:46.111 --> 33:48.417
[sighs]

33:53.161 --> 33:55.207
The ladle's left in the sink.

33:57.339 --> 33:59.167
Mom lets it soak.

33:59.211 --> 34:01.300
Leave it, she says.

34:01.343 --> 34:04.390
You go away,
and we come home.

34:04.433 --> 34:07.262
And what's left of you.
It loosens.

34:07.306 --> 34:09.830
And the water
carries it away.

34:09.873 --> 34:16.924
♪

34:20.406 --> 34:22.103
[water running]

34:22.147 --> 34:24.627
[phone buzzes]

34:26.151 --> 34:29.110
[phone buzzing]

34:29.154 --> 34:36.770
♪

34:36.813 --> 34:39.077
[phone buzzes]

34:47.302 --> 34:49.609
[sighs]

34:53.265 --> 34:58.661
♪

34:58.705 --> 35:00.489
[knocking]

35:00.533 --> 35:03.101
[inhales, exhales]

35:03.144 --> 35:05.277
[locks unlatching]

35:05.320 --> 35:10.804
♪

35:10.847 --> 35:17.245
They say girls with daddy
issues are really good in bed.

35:17.289 --> 35:18.725
- Mm.

35:18.768 --> 35:24.513
♪

35:24.557 --> 35:28.865
- I like who I am
with you, Joe.

35:28.909 --> 35:33.348
- ♪ You can see it
in my eyes ♪

35:33.392 --> 35:35.742
♪ On the level

35:35.785 --> 35:39.006
♪ Comin' out of nowhere

35:39.049 --> 35:43.184
♪

35:43.228 --> 35:45.534
- Mm, mm--sorry I didn't call.

35:45.578 --> 35:47.884
Is it okay if I come in?

35:51.149 --> 35:53.934
- ♪ I'm rebel

35:53.977 --> 35:58.199
♪ Take a breath
and say a prayer ♪

35:58.243 --> 35:59.853
- Ah! [laughs]

35:59.896 --> 36:03.291
- ♪ You play your game,
I take my time ♪

36:03.335 --> 36:04.814
- Ahh!

36:04.858 --> 36:08.340
- ♪ You take your aim

36:08.383 --> 36:12.344
♪ Commit your crime

36:12.387 --> 36:14.433
- Ahh!

36:14.476 --> 36:17.479
- Oh!
- [laughs] Ah!

36:17.523 --> 36:19.960
Too rough for you, Goldberg?

36:20.003 --> 36:21.222
- Not at all.

36:21.266 --> 36:23.442
- ♪ I'm a rebel

36:23.485 --> 36:28.142
♪ Comin' out of nowhere

36:28.186 --> 36:29.578
- Uh!
- Yeah!

36:29.622 --> 36:33.800
- ♪ Take a breath
and say a prayer ♪

36:33.843 --> 36:37.107
- [sighing]

36:39.371 --> 36:42.504
[sighs] I want you, Joe.

36:44.376 --> 36:47.205
- ♪ Comin' out of no--rebel

36:47.248 --> 36:50.469
♪ Comin' out of no--
rebel ♪

36:50.512 --> 36:53.167
♪ Comin' out of no--

36:53.211 --> 36:56.344
♪ Comin' out
of no-- ♪

36:56.388 --> 36:58.085
[both moan]

37:00.479 --> 37:03.438
[upbeat, light music]

37:03.482 --> 37:05.658
♪

37:05.701 --> 37:07.442
- [sighs]

37:07.486 --> 37:14.536
♪

37:17.539 --> 37:19.280
- Hey, stranger.

37:19.324 --> 37:21.630
- Ohh.

37:21.674 --> 37:23.284
- You drool in your sleep.

37:23.328 --> 37:25.504
So cute.

37:25.547 --> 37:27.375
- Were you watching me?

37:27.419 --> 37:30.030
- Maybe.

37:30.073 --> 37:32.337
- Uh-oh. Stalker.

37:32.380 --> 37:35.035
- Learn from the best.

37:37.777 --> 37:40.997
[sentimental music]

37:41.041 --> 37:46.089
♪

37:46.133 --> 37:48.962
[both laugh]

37:49.005 --> 37:52.270
- How--how did you
figure out where I live?

37:52.313 --> 37:53.401
- [sighs]

37:53.445 --> 37:56.404
The bearded guy
from the bookstore.

37:56.448 --> 37:58.493
- Oh.

38:01.801 --> 38:04.717
Mm, you taste like maple syrup.

38:09.635 --> 38:12.507
- Mm, wait.
- What?

38:12.551 --> 38:14.814
- [sighs]

38:16.424 --> 38:20.602
I have to apologize
about our talk.

38:20.646 --> 38:23.213
I was a hostile goose.

38:23.257 --> 38:24.563
- A hostile goose?

38:24.606 --> 38:26.565
- Yeah, geese are total dicks.

38:26.608 --> 38:28.349
But, uh, no, seriously.

38:28.393 --> 38:32.179
You called me on my shit,

38:32.222 --> 38:34.834
and I took it really poorly.

38:34.877 --> 38:37.402
Because, um--well, because

38:37.445 --> 38:39.360
you were totally right,
and I didn't wanna hear it

38:39.404 --> 38:40.622
and I'm sorry.

38:40.666 --> 38:42.407
- Like you said,
we barely know each other.

38:42.450 --> 38:44.278
And here I was, trying--
- You really don't think

38:44.322 --> 38:45.801
we know each other?

38:45.845 --> 38:48.413
I mean, I was just--I was angry
when I said that and--

38:48.456 --> 38:51.372
- Look...

38:51.416 --> 38:55.942
sometimes I could swear
I've known you forever.

38:55.985 --> 38:57.552
But in the grand scheme
of things,

38:57.596 --> 38:59.380
Not long enough

38:59.424 --> 39:00.686
for me to be commenting

39:00.729 --> 39:02.252
on your relationship
with your father.

39:02.296 --> 39:03.689
- Oh, you were just trying
to help me see

39:03.732 --> 39:06.431
that I'm full of shit.
[laughs]

39:06.474 --> 39:08.433
And you were sweet.

39:08.476 --> 39:12.393
Uh, it's funny. I feel like
every guy I date is--

39:12.437 --> 39:14.656
they're either messes--
like my dad was--

39:14.700 --> 39:16.310
or they're like my dad is now,

39:16.354 --> 39:21.010
trying to be something
that they think they should.

39:21.054 --> 39:22.447
Or they're me.

39:22.490 --> 39:24.405
Both a mess and a fraud.

39:24.449 --> 39:25.667
- You're not a fraud.

39:25.711 --> 39:28.670
- So just a mess?
- No, not more than anyone.

39:28.714 --> 39:31.891
- But then there is you.

39:31.934 --> 39:34.589
I mean, you're not trying to be
anything than what you are.

39:34.633 --> 39:37.157
You're just you.
There's not an ounce

39:37.200 --> 39:38.506
of falseness in you.

39:38.550 --> 39:42.031
I mean, you drink Cafe Bustelo
and you own starch.

39:42.075 --> 39:44.556
And I like how you don't care
about dumb shit

39:44.599 --> 39:46.601
like posting your life online.

39:46.645 --> 39:49.343
I mean, it's--
it's a revelation.

39:50.997 --> 39:55.218
Do you know how many selfies
I've taken on the toilet?

39:55.262 --> 39:56.394
A lot.

39:56.437 --> 39:58.439
[laughs]

40:01.007 --> 40:03.444
Okay, instead of sitting here,

40:03.488 --> 40:04.532
watching you judge me,

40:04.576 --> 40:06.360
I'm gonna go pee.
- No.

40:06.404 --> 40:07.448
I'm not--

40:07.492 --> 40:10.582
- And try not to take
a selfie.

40:12.235 --> 40:13.454
[door closes]

40:13.498 --> 40:14.673
- What are the chances

40:14.716 --> 40:16.457
I'm getting a follow-up
review?

40:16.501 --> 40:20.635
[upbeat pop music]

40:20.679 --> 40:23.638
- ♪ Heaven

40:23.682 --> 40:28.164
♪ I'm in heaven

40:28.208 --> 40:32.604
- Apparently
I've redeemed myself.

40:32.647 --> 40:34.083
Far be it for me to stop you

40:34.127 --> 40:36.869
from shouting it
from the rooftops.

40:36.912 --> 40:42.483
Plus, I guess it is nice
to hear it from your friends.

40:42.527 --> 40:44.137
Even if not all of them

40:44.180 --> 40:46.313
can share in your happiness.

40:46.356 --> 40:49.577
♪

40:49.621 --> 40:51.405
It's really too bad

40:51.449 --> 40:52.885
the one whose approval
you crave most

40:52.928 --> 40:54.539
isn't my biggest fan.

40:54.582 --> 41:01.894
♪

41:04.070 --> 41:09.684
Fortunately, Paco's a
remarkably quick reader.

41:09.728 --> 41:11.773
I can return the book I,
of course,

41:11.817 --> 41:14.733
never had any intention
of keeping.

41:14.776 --> 41:17.213
And if that's not enough,

41:17.257 --> 41:21.174
if Peach still
has a problem...

41:21.217 --> 41:23.132
well, every relationship has

41:23.176 --> 41:26.179
its obstacles to
overcome, right?

41:26.222 --> 41:29.225
I won't let her get
in the way of us, Beck.

41:29.269 --> 42:09.504
I won't.
